    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ADD-ON SLEEPER BOX - SLEEPER BOX - INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install washers and rubber insulators with the tapered side facing up in the sleeper
                mounting brackets.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a suitable hoist, position the sleeper box over the frame. Slowly lower the sleeper
                box onto the mounting brackets. Be sure to line up the sleeper box mounting bracket holes with the frame
                mounting bracket holes.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install four mounting bolts along with two washers for each bolt. Insert bolt and washer
                through top of the sleeper box mounting bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Working from under the frame mounting bracket, install spacer pipe, insulator retainer,
                insulator, flat washer and lock nut.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect hoist.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clamp heater duct assembly to cab outlet.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect air lines.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect wiring harness. Bolt on ground wire grommet.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install wiring harness retainers.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the opening boot assembly. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16008_7.xml" xrefid="hl1600802">SLEEPER BOX OPENING BOOT, INSTALL
                    <xref refid="hl1600802"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
